{
  "text": "Data sets consisted of 30 MRIs from healthy volunteers (15 women), scanned using a 1.5 Tesla GE Signa Echospeed scanner (GE Healthcare, Little Chalfont, Buckinghamshire, UK). The inversion recovery prepared fast spoiled gradient recall T1-weighted sequence yielded images with voxel sizes 0.9375 × 0.9375 × 1.5 mm [CITATION_1] , resliced in AC-PC orientation using windowed sinc interpolation to isotropic voxels with 0.9375 mm edge length. The median age was 30 years (range ; individual demographic characteristics of the sample are given in Table 1 .",
